PART 3: CONSTRUCTION STEPS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

STEP 1: PREPARE WOODEN TILES
• Cut 20 tiles from wood (5cm x 5cm x 0.5cm each)
• Sand all edges and surfaces until smooth
• Round corners slightly with sandpaper for safety
• Wipe clean of all sawdust

STEP 2: CREATE QUANTITY TILES (0-9)
• Lightly pencil guide marks for dot placement on 10 tiles
• Use red acrylic paint to create dots (8mm diameter)
• Use standard dice/domino patterns for arrangement
• Tile 0 remains blank (represents zero/empty set)
• Allow paint to dry completely (24 hours)

STEP 3: CREATE NUMERAL TILES (0-9)
• Lightly pencil center lines on remaining 10 tiles
• Write numerals 0-9 using black permanent marker (3cm tall)
• Ensure numerals are centered and legible
• Numerals should match style used in classroom (sans-serif recommended)

STEP 4: SEAL TILES
• Apply 2-3 coats of clear wood sealant to all tiles
• Allow drying time between coats (per sealant instructions)
• This protects paint/ink and allows for easy cleaning

STEP 5: FINISH TILES
• Attach small felt pads to bottom of each tile
• This prevents scratching and noise during use
• Test tiles on work surface to ensure smooth movement

STEP 6: PREPARE STORAGE TRAY
• Sand tray if needed
• Apply wood sealant or paint if desired (optional)
• Ensure compartments are clean and appropriately sized
• Label or mark divider if helpful for organization

STEP 7: QUALITY CHECK
• Verify all tiles are identical in size
• Check that dots are clear and evenly painted
• Ensure numerals are legible and correctly formed
• Confirm all tiles fit properly in storage tray
• Test that tiles can be easily grasped and manipulated

