PART 4: LESSON PRESENTATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

PREREQUISITES:

The child should have:
✓ Completed Number Rods (1-10)
✓ Completed Sandpaper Numbers (0-9)
✓ Experience with Spindle Boxes (understanding zero)
✓ Demonstrated one-to-one correspondence skills
✓ Interest in matching games or memory work

DIRECT AIM:
• Associate quantity with corresponding numeral (0-9)
• Strengthen number recognition
• Develop visual memory

INDIRECT AIM:
• Preparation for mathematical operations
• Development of concentration and focus
• Refinement of visual discrimination
• Building foundation for place value understanding

MATERIALS NEEDED:
• Number Memory Matching Game
• Work mat or small table
• Quiet work area

AGE: 4.5 - 6 years

