PART 5: VARIATIONS & EXTENSIONS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

VARIATION 1: MEMORY GAME (After Mastery)
• Place all tiles face-down in rows
• Take turns flipping two tiles
• Try to match quantity with corresponding numeral
• Develop visual memory and turn-taking skills

VARIATION 2: SEQUENCING PRACTICE
• Mix all quantity tiles
• Place in order 0-9 without looking at numerals
• Then verify with numeral tiles

VARIATION 3: SPEED MATCHING
• Time how long it takes to match all 10 pairs
• Child tries to improve personal best time
• Develops quick number recognition

VARIATION 4: PARTNER WORK
• One child arranges quantity tiles
• Partner finds matching numerals
• Promotes collaboration and peer learning

EXTENSION 1: ADDITION INTRODUCTION
• Select two quantity tiles (e.g., 3 and 2)
• Count all dots together (5)
• Find the numeral tile for the total
• "Three and two make five!"
• Early concrete addition practice

EXTENSION 2: CREATE OWN TILES
• Advanced children can create tiles for 11-20
• Combines quantities in teen board format
• Bridges to decimal system work

