PART 6: ASSESSMENT & OBSERVATION GUIDE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

READINESS INDICATORS:

Child is ready for this material when they demonstrate:
□ Can count objects 1-10 accurately
□ Recognizes numerals 0-9
□ Shows interest in matching activities
□ Can work independently for 10+ minutes
□ Understands concept of zero (empty set)

MASTERY INDICATORS:

Child has mastered this material when they can:
□ Correctly match all 10 pairs without assistance
□ Identify any quantity 0-9 by sight (subitizing)
□ Name any numeral 0-9 on sight
□ Complete matching in under 3 minutes
□ Work without checking each match multiple times
□ Self-correct any errors independently

OBSERVATION CHECKLIST:

During work, observe for:
□ Concentration span (aim for 10-15 minutes)
□ Self-correction behavior
□ Confidence level (does child seem sure or hesitant?)
□ Fine motor control (tile handling)
□ Verbal counting or silent work
□ Systematic approach vs. random matching
□ Frustration tolerance if errors occur
□ Pride in completed work

COMMON ERRORS & RESPONSES:

Error: Confusing 6 and 9
Response: "Let's check this numeral. The round part of the 9 is on top, like a balloon floating up. The round part of the 6 is on the bottom, like a ball on the ground."

Error: Miscounting dots on quantity tiles
Response: Don't point out error immediately. After all matching is done: "Let's check your work by counting together." Count dots together for mismatched tile. "How many did we count? What number should match?"

Error: Loses interest after few tiles
Response: Reduce set size. "Let's work with just five pairs today. You can do more tomorrow!"

