PART 8: MAINTENANCE & CARE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

DAILY MAINTENANCE:
• Wipe tiles with damp cloth if needed
• Ensure all tiles are returned to proper compartment
• Check that tiles are not chipped or damaged

WEEKLY MAINTENANCE:
• Deep clean tray and all tiles
• Verify all 20 tiles are present
• Replace any damaged tiles
• Check felt pads on tile bottoms

LONG-TERM CARE:
• Re-seal tiles annually if paint shows wear
• Touch up any faded numerals or dots
• Sand and refinish wooden tray as needed
• Store in dry location (avoid humidity which can warp wood)

EXPECTED LIFESPAN:
With proper care, this material should last 5-10 years of classroom use.

